The paper deals with the study of $k$-monotone functions, which are natural generalizations of the classical monotone functions, and their testing in the property testing model. This involves techniques from circuit complexity, learning theory, and distribution testing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper also draws connections to information theory (cs.IT) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
